1 Data Importing

1.1 Treasury yield curve data was imported from treasury.gov:

csvToXTS <- function(filename){
  yc <- data.table(read.csv(file = filename))
  yc[[1]] <- as.Date(yc[[1]])
  dates = yc[[1]]
  yc <- subset(yc, select = -c(Date) )
  yc <- xts(yc, order.by=dates)
  return(yc)
}

2 Data Processing

2.1 The daily returns are computed for the gold and equity ETFs:


gen_logret <- function(df){
  df$logret = log(df$Adj.Close/c(0, head(df$Adj.Close, -1)))
  df <- df[-1,]
  return(df)
}
gld <- gen_logret(gld)

5 Fitting the Yield Curve

6 Modeling Prices

Nelson-Siegel-Svensson yield curve formula for the forward rate:

\[\begin{array}{ccc} y_t(T) = \beta_{0} + \beta_{1} \exp\left( -\frac{T}{\tau_1} \right) + \beta_2 \frac{T}{\tau_1} \exp \left( -\frac{T}{\tau_1} \right) + \beta_3 \frac{T}{\tau_2} \exp \left( -\frac{T}{\tau_2} \right) \end{array}\]

MATURITY_BASES = c(2, 3, 5, 7, 10, 30)
A <- Svensson(yc, MATURITY_BASES )
Error in Svensson(yc, MATURITY_BASES) :

5.4 Significant changes to paramenters: It appears from the parameter graph, during the month of october, beta_3 rises from -20 to around -1. then during november it drops back to -20. Also, tau2 experiences changes. Around the end of october, value occasionally drop from 15 down to 3. It is those same daysoctober 28th and oct 29th that experience higher then average yield curvemeaning the structure of the curve didnt change but the entire curve rose upward.

idx = index(yc)
{
  for (i in seq_along(idx)){

  lines(MATURITY_BASES, yc[i,],col=2)
